  "final": {
    "status": "awaiting_approval",
    "rootCause": "The order-service is experiencing a cascading failure caused by a combination of undersized infrastructure capacity and a rigid connection pool design. Under elevated load, the service's fixed-size DB connection pool (no adaptive backoff) fills to its maximum, causing all subsequent DB checkout attempts to block or fail. With only 2 ECS tasks running and CPU already sustained above 90%, the service cannot scale to acquire more connections or process queued requests. The result is a feedback loop: pool saturation → checkout failures → increased latency → more queue buildup → further pool pressure. No recent code or config changes triggered this; it is a pure capacity and architectural resilience issue.",
    "remCount": 1
  }
